<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880222-0130 </DOCNO><HL> New America Offers Common Preferred, Notes Concurrently </HL><SO> </SO><CO> HYB </CO><IN> STK BON </IN><DATELINE> BOSTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   New America High Income Fund Inc. said it is offering concurrently 23 million common shares at $10 a share, 790 shares of taxable auction-rate preferred stock at $100,000 a share, and $105 million principal amount of senior extendible notes due Feb. 15, 1998, at a price of 100%.    The notes will bear interest at the rate of 9% per annum through Feb. 14, 1993, and thereafter at a rate and for a period to be determined by the fund.    The closed-end management investment company said proceeds from the offerings will be used for investment &quot;in accordance with the fund's investment objectives and policies.&quot;    Drexel Burnham Lambert Inc. is the sole underwriter of the preferred stock and senior notes. The common stock offering is being managed by Drexel Burnham, Bateman Eichler, Hill Richards Inc., Butcher andamp; Singer Inc. and Moseley Securities Corp. </TEXT></DOC>